headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 23 points, Jonathan Isaac played in an NBA game for the first time in 2 1/2 years and the Orlando Magic broke the Boston Celtics' nine-game winning streak Monday night with a 113-98 victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero, Isaac, Magic end Celtics' 9-game win streak 113-98

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 26 points in his 1,000th career game, Nikola Vucevic added 14 points and 17 rebounds and the Chicago Bulls beat the Atlanta Hawks 111-100 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan scores 26 in 1,000th game, Bulls beat Hawks 111-100

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored a career-high 42 points and the Houston Rockets held on for a 119-114 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Monday night to snap a 13-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green scores career-high 42, Rockets end 13-game skid

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen had 25 points and 11 rebounds, and the Utah Jazz beat the cold-shooting Charlotte Hornets 120-102 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen scores 25 as Jazz beat Hornets, who make only 2 3s

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 37 points and 12 assists, and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the San Antonio Spurs 147-127 on Monday night to stop a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard scores 37, Blazers beat Spurs 147-127 to stop skid

headlines.description: — Trey Lyles scored a season-high 24 points, Harrison Barnes had 15 of his 20 in Sacramento's record-tying first quarter and the Kings beat the short-handed Memphis Grizzlies 133-100 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings use early 3s, big 4th quarter to top Grizzlies 133-100
